---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Devoke's privacy policy. No personal data is collected. Your API key stays in your browser. No servers, no tracking, no accounts."
  canonical="https://devoke.app/privacy"
>
  <div class="policy-wrap">
    <header class="policy-header">
      <a href="/" class="policy-back" aria-label="Back to Devoke homepage">
        <span aria-hidden="true">←</span> Devoke
      </a>
    </header>

    <main class="policy-body container">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="policy-date">Last updated: March 2026</p>

      <section aria-labelledby="overview">
        <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
        <p>
          Devoke is a browser extension that runs entirely on your device. We do not operate
          servers that receive, store, or process your browsing data. There are no Devoke
          accounts and no analytics.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="data-collected">
        <h2 id="data-collected">What data Devoke handles</h2>

        <h3>Text content from web pages</h3>
        <p>
          When you browse X, Reddit, news sites, or Google Search, Devoke reads the text
          of posts and headlines visible in your viewport. This text is sent to Anthropic's
          API using your own API key to generate a rewritten version. Devoke does not store
          this text anywhere — it passes through in-memory only and is discarded when you
          close the tab.
        </p>

        <h3>Your Anthropic API key</h3>
        <p>
          Your API key is stored using <code>chrome.storage.sync</code>, which is managed
          by Chrome and may sync across your Chrome profile. The key is only ever sent to
          Anthropic's API endpoints — never to any Devoke server, because no Devoke server
          exists. Do not share your API key with anyone.
        </p>

        <h3>Extension settings</h3>
        <p>
          Your settings (enabled state, filter intensity, metric hiding preference) are
          stored in <code>chrome.storage.sync</code>. These preferences are local to your
          Chrome profile and are never transmitted anywhere.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="third-parties">
        <h2 id="third-parties">Third-party services</h2>
        <p>
          The only third-party service Devoke communicates with is the
          <strong>Anthropic API</strong> (<a href="https://www.anthropic.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Anthropic Privacy Policy</a>).
          Requests are made directly from your browser to Anthropic using your API key.
          Anthropic's data handling is governed by their own privacy policy.
        </p>
        <p>
          Devoke does not use Google Analytics, Sentry, Mixpanel, or any other analytics
          or error-tracking service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="permissions">
        <h2 id="permissions">Browser permissions</h2>
        <p>Devoke requests the following Chrome permissions:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Host permissions</strong> for X, Reddit, supported news sites, and Google
            Search — required to inject the content script that reads and rewrites page text.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>storage</strong> — to save your API key and settings via
            <code>chrome.storage.sync</code>.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Devoke does not request <code>history</code>, <code>cookies</code>,
          <code>tabs</code>, or any other broad permission.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="children">
        <h2 id="children">Children's privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Devoke is not directed at children under 13 and does not knowingly collect
          information from children.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="changes">
        <h2 id="changes">Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          If this policy changes in a material way, we will update the "Last updated" date
          at the top of this page. Continued use of the extension constitutes acceptance
          of the updated policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="contact">
        <h2 id="contact">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this policy? Open an issue on the
          <a href="https://github.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Devoke GitHub repository</a>
          or reach out directly.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .policy-wrap {
    background: var(--color-bg);
    min-height: 100svh;
  }

  .policy-header {
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(122, 184, 138, 0.08);
  }

  .policy-back {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--color-green);
    text-decoration: none;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    opacity: 0.8;
    transition: opacity 0.2s;
  }

  .policy-back:hover {
    opacity: 1;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .policy-body {
    padding-block: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 6rem);
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .policy-body h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .policy-date {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    max-width: 100%;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .policy-body section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .policy-body h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .policy-body h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .policy-body p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    max-width: 62ch;
    margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
  }

  .policy-body ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
  }

  .policy-body li {
    font-size: 0.93rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  .policy-body code {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 0.82em;
    background: rgba(122, 184, 138, 0.1);
    color: var(--color-green);
    padding: 0.1em 0.35em;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  .policy-body a {
    color: var(--color-green);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: rgba(122, 184, 138, 0.4);
  }

  .policy-body strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
</style>
